- `create_trap(...) -> bool`

## Effect Patterns Available
- `recover_lp` - Recover Life Points (param: amount)
- `damage` - Inflict damage to opponent (param: amount)
- `draw` - Draw cards (param: amount)
- `atk_boost` - Boost ATK of all your monsters (param: amount)
- `def_boost` - Boost DEF of all your monsters (param: amount)

## Best Practices
1. Always use SCOPE_OCG_TCG (0x3) for custom cards to show by default
2. Start card IDs at 10000100 or higher
3. **CRITICAL: Images MUST be `.jpg` format** - Game won't load `.jpeg`, `.png` works but `.jpg` is standard
4. Provide image URLs/paths when possible for automation
5. Test cards in-game immediately after creation
6. Keep card descriptions clear and concise
7. Use appropriate card types and subtypes
8. Follow official card naming conventions
9. Document complex custom effects in comments
10. Back up cards.cdb before bulk operations
11. Use consistent ID ranges for organization
12. **Store temporary utility scripts in `temp/` directory** (verify, update, search scripts)
13. When updating existing cards, use `db.update_card()` not `db.add_card()`
14. Set `$env:PYTHONIOENCODING="utf-8"` before running Python scripts on Windows

